image_analysis.description: A photograph of an interior staircase leading to a set of large, ornate double doors. The walls are made of light-colored stone blocks. To the left, there is a large framed landscape painting. A metal handrail runs along the left side of the stairs. To the right, there is another handrail and a doorway leading to another room. An umbrella stand with umbrellas is visible near the main doors. The ceiling has recessed lighting creating a warm glow.
image_analysis.layout: Vertical orientation showing a perspective view from the bottom of a staircase looking up toward a landing and a set of doors.

notes: The image is a photograph included in a document collection, identified by the Bates stamp EFTA00000850.
